      "id": "PopularPost43563",
      "post_content": "toward a7141988  \nit is not that useful with persist as a +1/+1 counter does not remove a -1/-1 counter, you would have to use another card to remove them. for what you described you would be better off with dross scorpian, power conduit and making an artifact creature have persist, kill the persisting artifact creature with the \"free-sac\" you mentioned which untaps the power conduit due to the scorpian's effect, the persisting artifact creature comes back and its counter gets removed by the conduit and turned into a +1/+1 or charge counter. but Blade of the Bloodchief has almost no bonus with persist besides you can kill the creature twice rather then only once.",
      "posted_by": "Lord_Xelitoth",
